              BIOL 314 Molecular Biology of Oncogenes (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-18790" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Biology (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Biology (Sci)              : The genes that cause cancer are altered versions of genes present in normal cells. The origins of these oncogenes, their genetic structure, regulation, and the biochemical properties of the oncogene-encoded proteins will be analyzed in an attempt to understand the origins of human and animal cancers.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
