                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/phar-599d1" class="program-course-title">
              PHAR 599D1 Pharmacology Research Project (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-33006" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Pharmacology and Therapeutics (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Pharmacology and Therapeutics              : Mechanisms involved in different pathologies and drug actions.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        R. Anne McKinney, Dusica Maysinger (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Fall</li>
              <li>Minimum of 9 hours/week to be spent in the lab and/or library.</li>
              <li>Pre-/Co-requisite: PHAR 562 and PHAR 563.</li>
              <li>Restriction: U3 students with permission of instructors; students should consult instructors 3 - 4 weeks before registration.</li>
              <li>Please see regulations concerning Project Courses.</li>
              <li>Students must register for both PHAR 599D1 and PHAR 599D2.</li>
              <li>No credit will be given for this course unless both PHAR 599D1 and PHAR 599D2 are successfully completed in consecutive terms</li>
              <li>PHAR 599D1 and PHAR 599D2 together are equivalent to PHAR 599</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

